From:Paul Senior
regarding defense stock ADG. recap.: They preannounced they would have lower
earnings and to a level they said was more normal level for their business: the
stock blew up (weak pun/wry grin). Slowly the stock came back over the past
weeks. Yesterday, they announced those poor earnings, and they were indeed poor
(imo). The stock has dropped sharply today.

I've begun adding back to my position.

The stock's now below book value (the only defense play I know that is). Debt's
manageable (imo), and the stock goes for a bit over 2x cash. The company's
profitable, and maybe there's some hope that the company's diversification away
from artillery shells might be working. (An electronic security subsidiary
reported receipt of a small (imo) order today.)

If the market isn't going to drop to lower levels (It seems to be today!), I'll
bet ADG stock will eventually rise again from today's $17.43. (OTOH, the
stock's thinly traded, so I'm guessing it could go much lower on just a
relatively few shares.)

http://finance.yahoo.com/q?s=adg
